{
  "text": "Memories of sun-lit copper roofs, laughing cousins and endless football created counter pictures to the brutality and ugliness of war. [CITATION_1] Still, stories of the good life in pre-war Bosnia were presented not as empty mantras, but as vivid and detailed accounts. Severe exceptionssickness, accidents, separations and death -were disclosed. A small number of families even made it clear that the child's early life had been harsh and troublesome. Thus, it seems reasonable that profile Prior to War captured at least the severely stressful in the child's early history.",
  "correct_citation": {
